# Lola case study — learn from past mistakes

**Scope:** This repo (`lola-case-study`) only. Do not commit or deploy unless the user asks.

## Source-of-truth order
1. **`HANDOFF_STORY_ARC.md`** — narrative: each beat said **once** on main scroll; depth → Reference only
2. **PDF export** (`Designing Lola · WhatsApp AI Assistant · Case Study.pdf`) — layout, density, visuals
3. **`HANDOFF_BOOK.md` / live wacrm** — production truth (what actually shipped)
4. Figma zip codegen — reference only; do not copy its IA or title

## Do not repeat these failures
- **Text-heavy rebuilds** — ownership tables, “What I shipped” essays, Proof chips, duplicate role lines
- **Wrong broadcast** — numbered CRM menu is *Before* only; production *After* uses Lola intro + tap buttons (`BROADCAST_LOLA_INTRO`)
- **Stacked FlowExplorer** — phone must not cover controls; **controls left, full 390px device phone right** (sticky)
- **Staff ops toggle** — PDF shows **both channels always** (staff WA + dashboard modal), not collapse/toggle
- **Reshuffling IA** — keep **ChapterNav** 4-phase timeline animation **unchanged**
- **Inventing sections** — no SolutionStrip, ImpactOutcomes, testimonials, Reference on main path unless asked

## Target layout (main path)
```
ChapterNav (unchanged)
Prologue → credentials + production truth (no Proof chip, no “What I shipped” line)
Define → horizontal service blueprint (6 cards), not ownership table
Discover → problem evidence (light)
Develop → FlowExplorer (production default) + StaffOps PDF layout
Deliver → ScrollTimeline + footer only
```

## Visual defaults
- WhatsApp mock: **390px device width**, chat scrolls inside frame
- Define: **flow diagram** from `SERVICE_BLUEPRINT`, not prose tables
- Production truth bento: must not clip long values (phone, URLs)

## Before claiming done
- Read `HANDOFF_STORY_ARC.md` skim test
- Compare mentally to PDF — visuals over copy
- `npm run build` in project root
- Do not add parallel “fixes” the user did not request
